{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://leoshcn.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"Ritva Auvinen (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that opera singer <b><a href=\"/wiki/Ritva_Auvinen\" title=\"Ritva Auvinen\">Ritva Auvinen</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> also worked as a gymnastics and swimming teacher?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ritva_Auvinen","retrieved":1772300573814},{"title":"Australasia (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that \"<b><a href=\"/wiki/Australasia_(poem)\" title=\"Australasia (poem)\">Australasia</a></b>\" by <a href=\"/wiki/William_Wentworth\" title=\"William Wentworth\">William Charles Wentworth</a>, the first book of verse by a native-born Australian, \"celebrates the development of a new Britannia in another world\"?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australasia_(poem)","retrieved":1772300573814},{"title":"Edward A. Brudno (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that Vietnam War prisoner <b><a href=\"/wiki/Edward_A._Brudno\" title=\"Edward A. Brudno\">Edward A. Brudno</a></b> was added to the <a href=\"/wiki/Vietnam_Veterans_Memorial\" title=\"Vietnam Veterans Memorial\">Vietnam Veterans Memorial</a> decades after his death following a <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense\" title=\"United States Department of Defense\">Department of Defense</a> ruling?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_A._Brudno","retrieved":1772300573816},{"title":"Girls' Last Tour (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the post-apocalyptic manga <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Girls%27_Last_Tour\" title=\"Girls' Last Tour\">Girls' Last Tour</a></b></i> has been described as an <i><a href=\"/wiki/Iyashikei\" title=\"Iyashikei\">iyashikei</a></i> ('healing') story?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Girls%27_Last_Tour","retrieved":1772300573817},{"title":"Takanashi Kiara (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the VTuber <b><a href=\"/wiki/Takanashi_Kiara\" title=\"Takanashi Kiara\">Takanashi Kiara</a></b> has attempted to take part in the Eurovision Song Contest multiple times?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Takanashi_Kiara","retrieved":1772300573819},{"title":"1946 Representative Council election in Bangui (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that Europeans and Africans voted in different buildings in the <b><a href=\"/wiki/1946_Ubangi-Shari_Representative_Council_election\" title=\"1946 Ubangi-Shari Representative Council election\">1946 Representative Council election in Bangui</a></b>?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1946_Ubangi-Shari_Representative_Council_election","retrieved":1772300573821},{"title":"Blanca Quiñónez (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Blanca_Qui%C3%B1%C3%B3nez\" title=\"Blanca Quiñónez\">Blanca Quiñónez</a></b>, the first player from South America in the history of <a href=\"/wiki/UConn_Huskies_women%27s_basketball\" title=\"UConn Huskies women's basketball\">UConn women's basketball</a>, speaks the <a href=\"/wiki/Molisan\" title=\"Molisan\">Molisan</a> dialect alongside Spanish, English, and Italian?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blanca_Qui%C3%B1%C3%B3nez","retrieved":1772300573822},{"title":"American Furniture Warehouse (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that it's \"none of your damned business\" how much <b><a href=\"/wiki/American_Furniture_Warehouse\" title=\"American Furniture Warehouse\">American Furniture Warehouse</a></b> paid <a href=\"/wiki/Billy_Carter\" title=\"Billy Carter\">Billy Carter</a>?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Furniture_Warehouse","retrieved":1772300573824},{"title":"Destination of the Month (Wikivoyage recommendations)","contents":"<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r4523569\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion\" about=\"#mwt7\" id=\"mwIQ\" data-mw=\"{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;templatestyles&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;Banner/styles.css&quot;},&quot;parts&quot;:[{&q